  "occasion": "Complete performance of the eleven Kamalamba Navavarana Kritis by Muthuswami Dikshitar (1775–1835), dedicated to Goddess Kamalamba of Thyagaraja Temple, Tiruvarur. Each kriti corresponds to one avaranam (enclosure) of the Sri Chakra, from the outermost Trailokyamohana to the innermost bindu. Preceded by invocatory kritis for Ganapati and Muruga, and concluded with a Mangala kriti. Dikshitar appears throughout as composer-in-residence.",
